</p>

<p corresp='TTP1814243P1' xml:id='OTP1814243P1'><rs ref='#S76166'>Corinth</rs> 25<add place='above'>th</add> 1862
</p>

<p corresp='TTP1814243P2' xml:id='OTP1814243P2'>To Maj. <rs ref='#S101699'>N. B Pearce</rs> C S.
</p>

<p corresp='TTP1814243P3' xml:id='OTP1814243P3'>Take possession of all sugar &amp; molasses at <rs ref='#S51785'>Jackson</rs> and <rs ref='#S25005897'>Big Black</rs> belonging to non residents parties and give the <rs ref='#S99413'>Rail Roads</rs> &amp; Agents of said parties receipts releasing them from Responsibility for it—Hold the sugar &amp; molasses subject to the order of Col. <rs ref='#S101700'>R. B. Lee</rs> Chief of Subsistence and report to him the quantity taken—I will instruct you by mail as to prices &amp; mode of payment
</p>

<p corresp='TTP1814243P4' xml:id='OTP1814243P4'><rs ref='#S101701'>J. E. Slaughter</rs><lb/>
Brig &amp; Insp Genl.
</p>

